htumsseiten.de/a-z/g/gloeckerllaufen/home.html (more information on the Glöcklerlauf)","quantity":null,"quantity_type":null}],"instructions":[],"cook_time":null,"serves":null},{"name":"Homemade Pie Crust","category":null,"ingredients":[{"content":"(1 cup) all-purpose flour","quantity":"225","quantity_type":"grams"},{"content":"(½ teaspoon) salt","quantity":"2,5","quantity_type":"ml"},{"content":"(1 cup) cold vegetable shortening","quantity":"230","quantity_type":"ml"},{"content":"(2 tablespoons) cold water (add 15 ml of water as needed)","quantity":"30","quantity_type":"ml"}],"instructions":["Combine flour and salt in medium bowl.","Cut in vegetable shortening with a pastry blender or two knives, until mixture is crumbly.","Sprinkle with cold water; blend until mixture holds together.","Shape dough into a ball; place on lightly floured surface.","Roll out dough to 3 mm (1/8 inch) thickness.","Line pie plate with pastry.","Trim around perimeter for 2 cm (1 inch) overhang to fold under and crimp as desired.","Fold overhang under and press down with your fingers.","Using the tines of a lightly floured fork, press the edge of the pastry to the rim of the pie pan.","Fold overhang under and pinch to make the edge stand up.","With the thumb and forefinger of one hand, pinch the outside edge of the pastry, while pressing from the inside with the forefinger of your other hand.","Fold overhang under and pinch to make the edge stand up.","Press the pastry along the edge of the pie plate between the side of your thumb at an angle, pinch and slightly twist."],"cook_time":null,"serves":null},{"name":"Homestyle Fried Potatoes","category":null,"ingredients":[{"content":"pound Russet potatoes, cut into 2 inch chunks","quantity":"1","quantity_type":null},{"content":"Salt and freshly ground black pepper","quantity":null,"quantity_type":null},{"content":"quarts olive oil (not extra virgin)","quantity":"2","quantity_type":null},{"content":"Sour cream (optional)","quantity":null,"quantit